    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Antibody kinetic curves obtained during a viral infection are often fitted using aggregated data from patients, hiding the heterogeneity of patient responses. The Wood equation makes it possible to establish the link between an individual\u2019s kinetic profile and the disease, which may be helpful in identifying and studying clusters.</jats:p>",
